<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - Before 12/06/1994 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - HOT WATER
        VALVE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>HOT WATER VALVE</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain engine cooling system.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cover from the passenger side of the instrument panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the cover from the Blend-Air unit.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the heater core as described in this section (
                    <hotlnk document="s16014_HL1601402.xml" xrefid="f1601413">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the control cable mounting screw from the mounting bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601414">Figure 14</hotlnk>). Disconnect the control cable from the Blend-Air door.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601414" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601414" filename="../figg16/g1601414.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="392px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 14. Hot Water Valve Connections</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. CABLE MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. CONTROL CABLE</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. HOT WATER FLOW CONTROL VALVE</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. HEATER CORE</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. BLEND-AIR DOOR</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. ADJUSTABLE LINK</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the hose clamp and disconnect the inlet hose (located under the Blend-Air
                    housing) from the neck of the hot water valve.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the hot water valve mounting screws. (Screw heads are located on the bottom of
                    the Blend-Air unit housing.)
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the control cable mounting bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect adjustable link from the Blend-Air door.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the hot water valve assembly as necessary to withdraw lower neck of the valve
                    through the grommet in the bottom of the Blend-Air unit housing. Remove the valve (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601415">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601415" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601415" filename="../figg16/g1601415.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 15. Hot Water Valve Removal</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. HOT WATER FLOW CONTROL VALVE</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. GROMMET</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the hose clamp and remove valve-to-heater core hose from the valve.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect all hoses and the water valve inlet grommet in the bottom of the housing. If
                    damaged or deteriorated, replace.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position water valve-to-heater core hose on the valve and tighten the hose clamp.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the lower neck of the hot water valve through the grommet in the bottom of the
                    Blend-Air door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the adjustable link to the Blend-Air door.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the flange of the cable bracket between the flange of the hot water valve bracket
                    and inside the wall of the unit housing. Align the screw holes.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the screws from outside the unit housing, through the cable mounting bracket and
                    into the tapped holes in the valve bracket. Tighten screws.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the inlet hose to the lower neck of the hot water valve and tighten the clamp.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the heater core. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16014_HL1601402.xml" xrefid="hl1601402">REMOVE AND INSTALL</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the control cable to the Blend-Air door and install the cable mounting screw.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Adjust the control cable. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16014_HL1601403.xml" xrefid="hl1601403">MAINTENANCE</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refill engine cooling system.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Set temperature control knob to HOT. Operate engine and check for coolant leaks and for
                    proper operation of the flow control valve.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace the covers on the Blend-Air unit and the instrument panel.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
